title: Fed Sees No Rate Hikes in 2019, Plans End to Balance Sheet Drawdown in September
text: Mar.20 -- Federal Reserve officials scaled back their projected interest-rate increases this year to zero and said they would end the drawdown of the central bank’s bond holdings in September after holding policy steady on Wednesday. Bloomberg's Mike McKee reports on "Bloomberg Markets."
